-- Instant View: ADP report up 192,000 in January
-- 
-- Wed Jan 30, 2013 8:58am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/30/us-usa-economy-instantview-idUSBRE90T0OZ20130130

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. private employers added 192,000 jobs in January, more than economists were expecting, in a sign of growth in the labor market, a report by a payrolls processor showed on Wednesday. 
 Economists surveyed by Reuters had forecast the ADP National Employment Report would show a gain of 165,000 jobs. December's private payrolls were revised down to an increase of 185,000 from the previously reported 215,000. COMMENTS: RAY STONE, ECONOMIST BONDS: U.S. treasuries declined, and the 10-year yield rose at 2.014 percent GRAPHIC: ADP vs. the U.S. Labor Department: The ADP National Employment Index shows an increase of 192,000 private sector jobs in January - 27,000 more than analysts expect Friday's Labor Department report to show.  link.reuters.com/fex44t (Americas Economics and Markets Desk; +1-646 223-6300)